# Trivy vulnerability suppressions.
# Each entry MUST document why the advisory does not apply and be re-checked
# whenever dependencies change. Trivy reads this file from the repo root, so it
# is honored by both the CI scans (docker-publish, cve-trivy-scan) and local runs.

# GO-2026-5932: golang.org/x/crypto/openpgp is unmaintained / unsafe by design.
# The package is NOT linked into our binary — `go list -deps ./cmd/goeland-server`
# reports zero openpgp packages. x/crypto is only pulled transitively via Echo's
# acme/autocert (auto-TLS), and Trivy flags this module-level advisory purely from
# the x/crypto module version in the binary's build metadata, not from reachable
# code. UNKNOWN severity, no fix available. Not applicable to this service.
GO-2026-5932
